#Corelatie partiala
X <- read.csv("sem4 date_logaritmate.csv",sep=",",header=TRUE,dec=".")
x<-X$rata.somajului
y<-X$nr.turisti.sositi
z<-X$venituri.gospodrii
cxz <- lm(x~z) 
rxz <- resid(cxz) 
cyz<-lm(y~z) 
ryz <- resid(cyz) 
cor(x,y) 
## [1] 0.02175228
cpxy <- cor(rxz,ryz)

cor_partiala_xy2=(cor(x,y)-(cor(x,z)*cor(y,z)))/sqrt((1-cor(x,z)^2)*(1-cor(y,z)^2))

date2 <- data.frame(x,y,z)
R<-cor(date2)
P<-solve(R) #inversa matricii R
cor_partiala_xy3 <- -1*P[1,2]/sqrt(P[1,1]*P[2,2])

#install.packages("cluster")
